      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <opener><dateline><date when="1914-11-19">Nov. 19, 1914</date></dateline>
              <salute>My dear <persName key="margaret_anderson">Miss Anderson</persName>:</salute></opener>
	        <p>I have heard nothing from you in answer to my letters of <date when="1914-10-25">October 25th</date> and <date when="1914-11-02">November 2nd</date>. In the first one I enclosed some of <persName key="richard_aldington">Richard Aldington’s</persName> poems for your consideration, and in the second one I suggested writing an article on the <orgName key="poetryBookshop">Poetry Book Shop</orgName> for your <title key="littleReview" level="j">magazine</title>. The mails are so poor that it is possible these letters have miscarried, but I should be very glad to hear from you about the matter if you have received them and if you have not I will send you copies of them.</p>
           <p>Your <date when="1914-11">November</date> issue is excellent. I agree with what <persName key="eunice_tietjens">Miss Tietjens</persName> says about the dangers of <foreign xml:lang="fr">vers libre</foreign>. Is it too soon to send you some more poems?</p>
            <closer>Sincerely yours,</closer>
         </div>
      </body>
